It was definitely one of those "you kinda had to be there" moments - all that I remember is that my dad was sorting Australian coinage to pay for bus fare, organizing it on his leg, while simultaneously telling some hilarious story. I love the expression on my face as I listen to the story. Somehow, he always makes the most mundane activities (like waiting for the bus) seem fun, and continues to brighten my world each and every day. I love you so much, Dad - Happy Father's Day!!!
